attributes.magic: PE32+ executable (GUI) x86-64, for MS Windows

exiftool.ImageFileCharacteristics: No relocs, Executable, Large address aware

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects malware by known bad imphash or rich_pe_header_hash
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Arnim Rupp

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a shellcode loader. The binary manually resolves API functions by parsing the PEB, hashing module and function names (ROR13 hash), and comparing them against a target hash. This is a common anti-analysis technique to hide its true functionality. After resolving the necessary functions, it allocates a new memory region with RWX permissions (PAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE) using 'VirtualAlloc', copies a payload into it, and then executes it. The presence of an RWX section (.bfav) and the dynamic API resolution are strong indicators of malicious activity.
